00:01:51,730 --> 00:01:55,760
Of course, as a fictional character, you can meet— Ah!

8
00:01:57,580 --> 00:01:59,160
In reality.

9
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,620
Ah, I am achy.

10
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:03,580
Ah, Sister-in-Law,

11
00:02:03,580 --> 00:02:05,930
- why are you coming out looking like a zombie? 
 - Brother-in-Law!

12
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:09,550
Are you okay?  You must've blacked out from drinking.

13
00:02:09,550 --> 00:02:11,230
Eat this.

14
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:17,690
- I just made it so— 
 - Ah, hot! 
 - It's really hot.  I just made it.

15
00:02:17,690 --> 00:02:20,140
- Water. 
 - Water?  Oh, water.

16
00:02:20,990 --> 00:02:23,980
If you are in this state, it's probably better you blacked out.

17
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:31,300
Oh, my head hurts.  I remember I came back in a taxi but...

18
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:33,570
Do you know how worried your sister was last night?

19
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:38,040
She gave me such a hard time because you weren't answering your phone.

20
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:40,160
Phone?

21
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:49,340
What is that?  Is that a thread or noodles?

22
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,160
It's noodles.

23
00:02:56,450 --> 00:02:58,180
What is this?

24
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:04,130

25
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:05,880
What—

26
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:08,370
Are you all right?

27
00:03:08,370 --> 00:03:09,440

28
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:12,060
- ₩100,000,000?! 
 - ₩100,000,000?

29
00:03:12,060 --> 00:03:14,180
What are you talking about, ₩100,000,000?

30
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,270
Agreement.  Kim Mooyoung.

31
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:23,890
Sister-in-Law, did you cause trouble again?

32
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:25,520
₩100,000,000?

33
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:33,270
Does it even make sense to ask for ₩100,000,000?  This uncle!

34
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:38,360
Sister-in-Law, where are you going? Sister-in-Law, where are you going? Sister-in-Law, where are you going?

35
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:43,520
I will make a plausible excuse for you to your sister!

36
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:46,100
Although you will die anyway.

37
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:51,030
♫  Starlight is falling down~  ♫

38
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:55,750
♫  Shalalalala  ♫

39
00:03:57,400 --> 00:04:01,760
♫  Shalalalala  ♫

40
00:04:07,230 --> 00:04:11,420
 Electricity bill, health insurance, gas bill.

41
00:04:11,420 --> 00:04:14,960
There are more bills to pay than income.

42
00:04:18,420 --> 00:04:24,850
When you watch dramas, even grim reapers and aliens all have their own house and car— 
  (T/N: he's referring to the K-dramas "Goblin" and "You Who Came From the Stars.")

43
00:04:29,050 --> 00:04:32,960
Why is my reality that of trying to make ends meet day-today?!

44
00:04:35,220 --> 00:04:38,970
But if I just get that settlement money from that crap...

45
00:04:38,970 --> 00:04:42,150
I should be okay for a little while.

46
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,110
Crap smell?!

47
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,660
 What is this?

48
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:30,590
We need to talk.

49
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:39,330

50
00:05:39,330 --> 00:05:41,520
Are you kidding me?!

51
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:45,600
It's good that you remember.

52
00:05:46,710 --> 00:05:48,590
What in the world are you thinking?

53
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:51,390
Don't you think this is too much?

54
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:55,820
- I just responded in the way you wanted. 
 - What I am saying is,

55
00:05:59,210 --> 00:06:04,710
what were you thinking asking for as much as ₩100,000,000?

56
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:10,030
Compensation for psychological damage, compensation for aftereffects from the accident.

57
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:15,240
Of course, I know very well that you can't convert psychological damage to a monetary value.

58
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:18,140
And I admit that I am at fault for throwing the helmet, but...

59
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:20,900
isn't ₩100,000,000 too much?!

60
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:33,320
Can you just give a little... discount?

61
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:38,780
How much?

62
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:44,190
I really am not saying this because I don't have the money.

63
00:06:44,190 --> 00:06:48,700
I am going to give you the settlement money. But to be honest,

64
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:54,840
it's just that yesterday I quit my job at the broadcast station...

65
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:58,070
  - What is this smell?  
 - So I can't right now...

66
00:06:59,330 --> 00:07:04,090
 Those clothes, covered with drops of kimchi soup and all kinds of pollutants, that haven't been laundered for at least a week...

67
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:07,550
 and that seborrheic scalp that has been neglected for more than 4 days...

68
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:09,540
 - And this smell—  
 - To be honest, I am...

69
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:12,520
 - It's not a smell that comes from a human.  
 - ...right now...

70
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:16,360
- ...having a little bit of a hard time. 
   - The smell of poverty that is emanating from deep inside...

71
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:18,200
Quite a bit of a hard time...

72
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:21,080
 Really sad state...

73
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:26,060
I have to dig a hole to pay another with credit card debts as well...

74
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:29,680
And I will get kicked out of the house if I can't take care of this month's living expenses.

75
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:32,340
My sister is no joke.

76
00:07:32,340 --> 00:07:35,720
 This human looks like she has it harder time making ends meet than I do.

77
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:39,190
 What was I expecting from this human who looks like she doesn't even have ₩1, let alone ₩100,000,000?

78
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:45,110
I... will somehow get together the settlement money, so if you could please wait a few days—

79
00:07:45,110 --> 00:07:47,920
no, a few weeks?

80
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,290
A few months?

81
00:07:51,290 --> 00:07:54,360
Leave.  Let's forget the whole thing.

82
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:58,260
- What are you doing now?  Forget the whole thing?  We can't do that—
 - Why not?

83
00:07:58,260 --> 00:08:00,530
I said we can.  So just leave, please.

84
00:08:00,530 --> 00:08:03,180
- Hey, look here, Mister— 
 - I said leave.

85
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:05,480
- I said leave. 
 - No, the settlement money—

86
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,220
- Leave. 
 - Uh!

87
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,290
Wait, Mister!

88
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:18,700
He doesn't have to go so far as to forget the whole thing...

89
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:22,020
Making me feel bad....

90
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:33,030
I am a crazy punk for expecting anything.

91
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:37,820
  Aftermath of crap, reality came knocking.

92
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:54,120
 For a zombie to make a living...

93
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,790
 is that the only way?

94
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:58,490

95
00:08:58,490 --> 00:09:00,620
Are you sure?

96
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,510
Yeah.

97
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:04,700
Hey, tell me the details.

98
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:07,740
There is a dog that the elementary school was taking care of.

99
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:13,190
Detective Kim Mooyoung found it, so the young friends are all talking about it.

100
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:15,960
But where did the kids get the money?

101
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:19,530
He only charged ₩500 for finding the dog.

102
00:09:19,530 --> 00:09:21,470
He really is awesome, isn't he?

103
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:23,460
Unlike somebody I know, he has great character...

104
00:09:23,460 --> 00:09:25,380
Great?

105
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:27,990
If he is that great, why don't you go and work for Detective Kim!

106
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:30,760
Go across the street right now, you punk!

107
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:36,720
I will at least work as much as I got paid in advance.

108
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:40,630
This damned decisive punk!

109
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,090
₩500?

110
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:50,900
Detective Kim, you won't do.

111
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:53,780
If you price dump like this,

112
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:56,870
are you telling other detective agencies to fold business or what?

113
00:09:57,950 --> 00:10:02,500
You want to be the sole business?  To me, Lee Sung Rok,

114
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,440
you are declaring a war?

115
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:57,960

116
00:11:05,580 --> 00:11:09,660
 Until I find my past, I have to zom-buh (endure like a zombie with tenacious vitality) in this neighborhood.

117
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:14,890
 In order to zom-buh, I have to earn money myself.

118
00:11:16,730 --> 00:11:18,670
This teacher studied abroad in Italy.

119
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:21,660
Hey, young man, take this.

120
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:23,310
We have skilled teachers.

121
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:28,210
Oh, hello, young man!  They say he studied overseas, in Italy.

122
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:29,390
My goodness, Miss!

123
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:31,510
 It is a capitalist's smile from much experience.

124
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:36,220
The study academy at the corner. He studied overseas, in Italy...

125
00:11:39,590 --> 00:11:41,560
He teaches from the basics.

126
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,340
Miss! Here, here!

127
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:46,820
Bring the kids.

128
00:11:46,820 --> 00:11:49,570
 I cannot seriously take this anymore.

129
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:09,520
Hey!

130
00:12:11,950 --> 00:12:14,290

131
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:23,900
Amazing!

132
00:12:27,270 --> 00:12:29,240
What's going on?

133
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,430
What were you doing so early in the morning that you don't even answer your phone?

134
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:37,260
It's just that I had to go somewhere.

135
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:39,620
You drank again last night, didn't you?

136
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:45,400

137
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:48,130
Here.

138
00:12:51,810 --> 00:12:53,930
It's nice!

139
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:56,360
So, any new information on the attacker?

140
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:59,110
Are you curious about that even now?

141
00:13:00,210 --> 00:13:05,790
It's a construction site so there is no CCTV and, same as before, there was no evidence left behind at the crime scene.

142
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:11,460
Ah, he made the difficult choice to do the interview because of me...

143
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:16,720
He went on the broadcast program then got attacked.  What witness would get the courage to come forward?

144
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:21,540
I will catch the culprit,

145
00:13:21,540 --> 00:13:23,870
so you just take care of yourself.

146
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:38,130
Are they putting together a dedicated team?

147
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:42,850
The Violent Crimes Unit is also investigating, right? What about wanted posters?

148
00:13:42,850 --> 00:13:47,200
Ah, what if the investigation closes early like last time?

149
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,580
Each and every case is important to us!

150
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:53,390
But if we don't have enough evidence, there is going be a limit to our investigation.

151
00:13:53,390 --> 00:13:55,240
I know.

152
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:59,990
You don't have enough manpower per case and you can't do anything without a search warrant.

153
00:13:59,990 --> 00:14:03,120
But what if you fail to catch him again?

154
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:06,530
What if someone else is sacrificed?

155
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:13,260
We have to find that bastard fast.

156
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,020
How in the world are we going to find him?

157
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,010
You just have to hire a detective.

158
00:14:17,010 --> 00:14:20,330
The detective can find anything if you give him money.

159
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:23,510
Detective Uncle even found Hodoo in just one day

160
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:25,720
when the police couldn't.

161
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,900
Detective Uncle is the best!

162
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:30,760
Our Joonwoo, come here!

163
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:32,430
You even know a detective?

164
00:14:32,430 --> 00:14:35,020
Our Joonwoo is the best!

165
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,140
Ah, Director Lee.  Ah, sorry, sorry.

166
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:42,230
I forgot.

167
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:45,310
- Did you wait for long? 
 - No, I didn't.

168
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:49,160
I get forgetful.

169
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,880
I read the script well.  It's really fun.

170
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:53,900
Thank you, Mr. CEO.  I will work hard to make the film.

171
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:58,910
But it's going to be difficult for me to make it.

172
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:02,430
But you said you had fun reading it.  Why not—

173
00:15:02,430 --> 00:15:04,070
It was fun.

174
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:08,530
So, this basically is a story about a zombie taking revenge against the humans who made him that way, right?

175
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:10,440
Yes, that's right.  It's a zombie noir.

176
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,340
Ah, zombie noir?

177
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:13,210
- Noir.  Yes. 
 - Wow, it's cool.

178
00:15:13,210 --> 00:15:16,360
It's nice.  It's cool.

179
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:19,130
But there are a few things that are bothering me as well.

180
00:15:19,130 --> 00:15:20,360
What things?

181
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:22,860
Isn't it a bit strange for a zombie to attend a Catholic church?

182
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:27,000
Wearing a veil and all?   It could become a sensitive religious issue.

183
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,580
I will take it off.

184
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:30,370
- Take off what? 
 - I will take the veil off.

185
00:15:30,370 --> 00:15:32,370
So that there is no religious issue, I will go with no religion.

186
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:34,520
Oh, that's good.

187
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:35,720
No religion is good.

188
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:40,400
But other than that, as a whole...

189
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,710
isn't this beautifying the zombie?

190
00:15:42,710 --> 00:15:46,070
How and in what way did I beautify the zombie?

191
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:50,940
Zombies eat human intestines.  It's not a hero...

192
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:56,250
Mr. CEO, the zombie that I wrote about...

193
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:59,190
has deep pain, is lonely, and...

194
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:02,830
he even sacrifices himself for someone he loves.  He is a romantic zombie.

195
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:08,450
What zombie is a romantic?

196
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,840
But how do I explain this?

197
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:13,160
- Director Lee, you watched "Walking Dead," right? 
 - Yes.

198
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:18,020
"Train to Busan," "Peninsula." Zombies attack in groups, get chased, and get shot to death...

199
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:20,440
This is what the audience wants.  Exhilarating.

200
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:26,290
But there are so many zombie works that are like that.  I want to write about a different kind of zombie.

201
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:28,430
It is different.  I like it because it is different.

202
00:16:28,430 --> 00:16:30,680
It is different.  Too different.

203
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:34,370
Director Lee, you tended to be ahead of your time.

204
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:36,800
You are right.  That is sometimes a problem for me.

205
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:39,740
But I think it is a good thing to be ahead of my time.

206
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:44,310
I like it but I don't know how to convince the investors.

207
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:47,910
To say it bluntly, unless you find some blind investors from somewhere...

208
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:51,460
Mr. CEO, I will find blind investors.

209
00:16:51,460 --> 00:16:55,210
Then the movie can be made, can't it?

210
00:16:55,210 --> 00:16:56,790
Ah, of course.

211
00:16:56,790 --> 00:16:59,100
Ah, that's a relief.

212
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,920
Call me when you find them.

213
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:05,140
I will find them for sure.

214
00:17:14,890 --> 00:17:15,890
What about what you promised?

215
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:18,410
A man doesn't go back on his words.

216
00:17:18,410 --> 00:17:20,730

217
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,640
₩5,000 per hour, right?

218
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:32,490
Honor your promise about time.

219
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:43,680
 I should at least be able to buy the cream for disguise with this money.

220
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,940
They say a dog's life is the best and it's a carefree life...

221
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:53,480
Great Profit is even happier than this zombie.

222
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:55,340
You put on some weight, what did you eat?

223
00:17:55,340 --> 00:17:57,560
Did you have something delicious?

224
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:36,870
What is going on?  How did you get in?

225
00:18:36,870 --> 00:18:38,960
Please drink this.

226
00:18:40,130 --> 00:18:43,650
You must have been distributing your business cards.  It is tiring, isn't it?

227
00:18:43,650 --> 00:18:46,260
 It's giving me the chills... this crap.

228
00:18:46,260 --> 00:18:47,910
We are already done with the settlement talk, so leave.

229
00:18:47,910 --> 00:18:50,470
I am not here because of the settlement.

230
00:18:50,470 --> 00:18:53,750
I have something to ask you.

231
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:56,330
Make it fast and just leave.

232
00:18:56,330 --> 00:19:00,750
I did the broadcast program on the "Santa" kidnapping case.

233
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:02,240
There is something I need to find related to the case,

234
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:05,300
if I could ask for a consultation.

235
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,530
2,000 for a human, 500 for an animal.

236
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,220
I am not saying that I will hire you for sure.

237
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:16,510
Before that, if I could get a consultation...

238
00:19:16,510 --> 00:19:20,370
 She is the worst of the fleas.  I need to get rid of her before she clings on to me.

239
00:19:20,370 --> 00:19:23,490
I am sorry but that will be difficult.  Please leave.

240
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:26,010
Uh, wait just a moment, please!

241
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:31,540
- Is it okay to chase a customer out like this? 
 - Yeah, it's okay. So leave. (T/N: speaking informally)

242
00:19:31,590 --> 00:19:34,980
Excuse me, but why do you keep speaking informally to me?

243
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:36,340
Then if it were you,

244
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:40,960
would you speak formally after getting hit with a helmet and breaking your head?

245
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,080
You are right.

246
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,720
Please speak comfortably and informally.

247
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:46,030
I will, so please leave.

